.TH "pt_buffer_setup_aux" 9 "pt_buffer_setup_aux" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pt_buffer_setup_aux \- set up topa tables for a PT buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" pt_buffer_setup_aux
.BI "(struct perf_event *event "  ","
.BI "void **pages "  ","
.BI "int nr_pages "  ","
.BI "bool snapshot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "event" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "pages" 12
Array of pointers to buffer pages passed from perf core.
.IP "nr_pages" 12
Number of pages in the buffer.
.IP "snapshot" 12
If this is a snapshot/overwrite counter.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a pmu::setup_aux callback that sets up ToPA tables and all the
bookkeeping for an AUX buffer.
.SH "RETURN"
Our private PT buffer structure.
